         <abstract>
            <p>Galerkin approximations to solutions of a Cauchy-Dirichlet problem governed by the generalized porous medium equation &lt;tex-math&gt;$\frac{\partial u}{\partial t} \sum^N_{i=1}\frac{\partial}{\partial x_i}(|u|^{\rho}-2\frac{\partial u} {\partial x_i})=f(x,t)$&lt;/tex-math&gt; on bounded convex domains are considered. The range of the parameter ρ includes the fast diffusion case &lt;latex&gt;$1 &lt; \rho &lt; 2$&lt;/latex&gt;. Using an Euler finite difference approximation in time, the semi-discrete solution is shown to converge to the exact solution in L&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt; (0,T; L&lt;sup&gt;ρ&lt;/sup&gt;(Ω)) norm with an error controlled by O(Δ t&lt;sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;1/4) for &lt;latex&gt;$1 &lt; \rho &lt; 2$&lt;/latex&gt; and &lt;tex-math&gt;$O(\Delta t^\frac{1} {2\rho}$&lt;/tex-math&gt;) for 2 &lt;latex&gt;$\leq \rho &lt; \infty$&lt;/latex&gt;. For the fully discrete problem, a global convergence rate of O(Δ t&lt;sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;1/4) in L&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;(0,T; L&lt;sup&gt;ρ&lt;/sup&gt;(Ω)) norm is shown for the range &lt;latex&gt;$\frac{2N}{N+1} &lt; \rho &lt; 2$&lt;/latex&gt;. For &lt;latex&gt;$2 \leq \rho &lt; \infty$&lt;/latex&gt;, a rate of O(Δ t&lt;sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;1/2ρ) is shown in L&lt;sup&gt;ρ&lt;/sup&gt;(0,T; L&lt;sup&gt;ρ&lt;/sup&gt;(Ω)) norm.</p>
          </abstract>
